<br>
Think of it this way.  If you were God, and wanted to create a Universe with beings that were self-aware and interesting to you, would you write a play (the idea that fate is written and God has scripted everything in advance), or make a free will universe where those beings could make their own choices?<br>
<br>
I believe God has the power to intervene when He wishes.  Why didn't he intervene on Tuesday?  Perhaps the greater good will be served by the world uniting against terrorism, perhaps humanity as a whole has something to learn from this and other tragedies that we cannot learn otherwise.  I believe humanity learned much from the horrors of the last century that we would not know otherwise.  Death is only *bad* if one believes that after death there is nothing, or only suffering.  It is bad to us because we do not know what is beyond, and we are scared.<br>
<br>
Coincidentally, as someone pointed out, Chirstianity does not believe in weighing out sin.  God's Grace can change people's hearts so that they do not want to commit as much sin and can cause those people to make changes that affect the world.  That is God's will and done by the power of God, but again, done in a manner of free will, and no hand of God comes down to move a mountain or pull someone's puppet strings.<br>
<br>
I do not have it all figured out.  I doubt my faith on occassion.  I do not always follow God's message in my heart,  I often do not even try to listen.  I still sin.  Alot.  I do not throw Bibles at people.  I do not believe in extremism in Christianity nor Islam.  I think the Spanish Inquisition would be as bad today as the Jihad.  I think neither of those understand what God's grace truly is.<br>
<br>
If you want to flame me because my ideas are unsound to you, that is your right.  But if you want to flame me or think less of me just because I have actually devoted deep thought (right or wrong) to something as important as the possibility of God and eternity, you are a fool.<br>
<br>
